Flourishment
body:
The next Flourishment event will answer, “What are the core elements of a flourishing business?” Learn more and register at leafinstitutegreenville.org.

In 1944, the owners of seven Napa Valley vineyards did something that had never happened before. They started meeting together monthly and sharing what they knew about making wine. You see, Napa Valley had been making wine for about 100 years by that point, but it had never been any good. They wanted it to be great. 

So what happened? After only three decades of getting together, two Napa Valley wines won a blind tasting at the international wine competition in Paris. The Europeans were shocked. How was such a thing possible, and in such a short amount of time? 

Some of us in town love that Napa Valley story. We’re not in the wine business, but we know there are a lot of great businesses doing wonderful things here in the Upstate. We also know that we’re not usually spending time together, not learning from one another. 

That’s why some business leaders in Greenville started an event called Flourishment. It’s a monthly luncheon for local business leaders who care about human flourishing. April will be our third month, and we’ve already hosted talks and conversations with leaders from companies that do building, architecture, coffee, motorsports, marketing, tree care, and many other industries. Flourishment is hosted by the Leaf Institute, a center for faith, vocation and art in the Village of West Greenville.

title: Church Picnic
body:
Celebrate the coming of summer by joining us for an evening picnic in Cleveland Park.

We will gather at Shelter #29 (view location HERE), near the Greenville Zoo. We will have easy access to parking, restrooms, and a large playground.

We will enjoy pulled pork, mac & cheese, green beans, and banana pudding from Henry’s BBQ. Individual portions of alternative options are available–please contact Maddie Searcy if you would like to request an alternative meal.

title: Women's Summer Book Study
body:
WHAT:  We are going to read Liturgy of the Ordinary by Tish Warren, and discuss together on Monday nights this summer. Some of you are already reading it, so it will be fresh! It’s a compelling and very practical book!
Grab a copy off Amazon today or check it out from the public library.

WHEN: We’ll meet in different homes starting the week of June 3 through August 19 @ 7:30pm. We are going to take the last Monday of each month off, and will most likely have some kind of social hang out that week.
We are still working on host homes, so we will email you with these details closer to time. Contact Brittany Aills if you would like to volunteer to host.

WHO: All women are invited! Friends, neighbors, co-workers especially! This is a very easy thing to invite a non-Christian to come with you. 

Please register below so we can get a feel for numbers/space needs. With travel schedules, it will be helpful to know, but feel free to pop in when you can! We know summer can be very busy, but wanted to offer a way for women to still connect.

Register by clicking below. Children needing nursery care must be registered by Friday, November 8.

REGISTER

title: Women's Lunchtime Bible Study
body:
We will resume Women’s Bible Study as usual the first week of September and end the week of November 11. Light lunch provided.

This will be an 11-week series to finish out the book of John. We’ll be picking back up with John 11, but don’t let this stop you from coming for the first time! You can purchase a book HERE and jump right in to any of the offered times. ALL are always welcome.
